Yellow fever - Peru 19950616.0421
Date: Thu 7 Jun 2001 11:28:12 -0400
From: Marianne Hopp <mhopp@iri.columbia.edu>
Source: WHO Disease Outbreaks Report, Thu 7 Jun 2001 [edited
<http://www.who.int/disease-outbreak-news/n2001/june/7june2001.html>

Yellow Fever Outbreak in the Amazon Region of Peru
--------------------------------------------------
The Ministry of Health has reported an outbreak of yellow fever in the
Department of Loreto, in the Peruvian Amazon Region, in the districts of
Puinahua, San Pablo and Iquitos. In total 8 cases have been laboratory
confirmed, of which 2 have died. Another 12 cases are under investigation.
An epidemiological investigation is underway and the WHO Regional Office
for the Americas (PAHO) has mobilized 400 000 doses of vaccine for a
vaccination campaign.
--
